functions.label: createToolProvider
description: Utility function to create a {@link ToolProvider} from a list of tools.

interfaces.label: AsyncProvider
description: Generic async provider interface

interfaces.label: BaseWorkflowDefinition
description:
Describes the definition of a workflow.

This is only meant to be the "pure" definition. Persistence related things (e.g. id),
or ownerId will be on higher-level structures.

children.label: id
description: A unique ID that can be used to reference this workflow.

children.label: name
description:
The name of the workflow.

Should be human (and LLM) readable, e.g. "Salesforce Case Summarization".
Will be exposed to the LLM in some situations.

children.label: description
description:
A short description of what this workflow does.
Will be exposed to the LLM in some situations (e.g. assistant orchestrator or intent detection step)

children.label: inputs
description: List of inputs for this workflow.

children.label: outputs
description: List of outputs for this workflow.

interfaces.label: BuiltInNodeDefinition
description: A definition for a builtIn node, bound to the corresponding configuration schema.

children.label: id
description: Unique ID for this node, within the workflow definition

children.label: type
description: The type of node.

children.label: description
description: Optional description of what the node does in the workflow

children.label: configuration
description: Specific configuration for this node's type.

interfaces.label: FunctionWorkflowDefinition
description:
Function workflows allow arbitrary function execution as workflows.

Can be used to "import" a workflow in the framework.

children.label: type
description: Unique type identifier for function workflows

children.label: handler
description: The function handler that should be called to execute the workflow.

interfaces.label: FunctionWorkflowHandlerParams
description: Arguments for a function workflow.

children.label: inputs
description: The inputs for the workflow

children.label: eventHandler
description: Event handler that can be used to send custom workflow events

children.label: type
description: Unique type identifier for graph workflows

children.label: steps
description: Configuration for each of the workflow's nodes.

interfaces.label: IntentRecognitionNodeConfigType
description: Config for `intentRecognition` node type.

children.label: prompt
description: The prompt explaining the LLM the criteria for its choices

children.label: branches

interfaces.label: LoopNodeConfigType
description: Represents the configuration for a `loop` node.

children.label: inputList
description:
Reference of the context variable to loop over.
Supports interpolation. If interpolated value is a list,
will use it directly. If interpolated value is a string,
will retrieve the corresponding entry in the current state.

children.label: itemVar
description:
Name of the state property to inject the current loop element into.
Supports interpolation, but final value must be a string.

children.label: steps
description: The sequence of steps to execute for each element in the list.

children.label: output
description:
If defined, will accumulate results from each loop iteration,
by reading the `output.source` context property in the loop's state,
and creating a `output.destination` array in the parent's state.

interfaces.label: ModelProvider
description:
Provider, allowing to select various models depending on the needs.

For now, only exposes a single default model type.

children.label: getDefaultModel
description: Returns the default model to be used for LLM tasks.

interfaces.label: NodeEventReporter
description: Event reporter that can be used to report real time progress, or telemetry events from a node run.

interfaces.label: NodeFactoryBaseServices
description: Base set of (pre-scoped) services that will always be exposed to the node factory.

children.label: logger
description:
Logger scoped to this node.

Note: logging from within workflows is mostly for debugging purposes.
progression and telemetry events should be used instead for other usages.

children.label: modelProvider
description: Provider exposing LLM models to be used.

children.label: toolProvider
description: Provider exposing tools that are available in that given context (workflow/node)

children.label: esClusterClient
description: Scoped cluster client.

children.label: workflowRegistry
description: Registry exposing the workflows accessible in the node's context.

children.label: nodeRegistry
description: Registry exposing node types, can be used to access node type definitions.

children.label: workflowRunner
description:
Scoped node runner, can be used to run nodes as part of a node's execution flow,
e.g. for conditional nodes.

interfaces.label: NodeFactoryContext
description: Context that is exposed to a {@NodeRunnerFactory} function.

children.label: nodeConfiguration
description: The (non-interpolated) configuration bound to this node.

children.label: services
description: Scoped services that can be used by the factory.

interfaces.label: NodeRunner
description: Represents an instance of a node runner.

children.label: run
description: Run the node with the provided inputs.

interfaces.label: NodeTypeDefinition
description:
Represents the definition for a given node type.

Similar to SOs, vis types and so on, this defines all the properties
and handlers that are going to be used to manage the lifecycle of a node type.

children.label: id
description: The unique identifier for this node type (it's type)

children.label: name
description: Human-readable name for this node type

children.label: description
description: Short human-readable description for this node type.

children.label: factory
description: The {@link NodeRunnerFactory} for this node type.

children.label: customServicesProvider
description:
Allows defining a handler to return arbitrary services that will be exposed to
the {@link NodeRunnerFactory} via it's context, {@link NodeFactoryContext}.

This can be used as a convenient way to pass down additional services to
the node factory and runner, for situations where the node type might need
to access those services during its execution.

interfaces.label: ParallelSequencesNodeConfigType
description: Config for `parallelSequences` node type.

interfaces.label: PromptNodeConfigType
description: Config for `prompt` node type.

interfaces.label: Provider
description: Generic provider interface

interfaces.label: Registry
description: Generic registry interface

interfaces.label: RunNodeParams
description: Param type for {@link NodeRunner.run}

children.label: input
description: raw input (configuration for this node, as described in the configuration

children.label: state
description:
Global state for this run.

Usually, nodes don't need to access this directly, as the node's configuration
should be sufficient for the framework to inject the right properties,
but the state is still exposed to the nodes during execution

children.label: eventReporter
description: Event reporter for this run.

children.label: executionState
description:
The current workflow execute state.
Can be used when manually throwing errors from the node run handler.

children.label: runId
description:
The runId that was bound to this run. Can be used to find events in
tracing / telemetry or so on.

children.label: output
description: The output from the workflow.

children.label: id
description: The ID of the workflow to run.

children.label: inputs
description:
The inputs to execute the workflow with.
Inputs will be validated against the defined schema.

children.label: request
description: The request that initiated that run.

children.label: toolProvider
description:
If specified, the workflow runner will use
tools from this provider in addition to the default ones when
running the workflow.

Can be used to expose custom tools.

children.label: onEvent
description:
Optional event handler to handle workflow execution events.

Can be used to handle progression events in real time.

children.label: defaultConnectorId
description:
If specified, will use that connector as the default connector
instead of picking the default one automatically.

interfaces.label: ScopedRunner
description:
An internal runner scoped to the current workflow execution context.
Can be used to have nodes execute workflows or node definitions as part of their execution.
E.g. for conditional nodes, parallel nodes or other...

Exposed to node execution via the {@link NodeFactoryBaseServices}.

children.label: runWorkflow
description: Run a workflow definition, using a context bound to the current execution flow.

children.label: runNode
description: Run a node definition, using a context bound to the current execution flow.

interfaces.label: ScopedRunnerRunNodeParams
description: Params for {@link ScopedRunner.runNode}

children.label: nodeDefinition
description: The definition of the node to run.

children.label: state
description: The state passed to the node.

interfaces.label: ScopedRunnerRunWorkflowParams
description: Params for {@link ScopedRunner.runWorkflow}

children.label: workflowDefinition
description: The definition of the workflow to run.

children.label: inputs
description: The input passed to the workflow.

interfaces.label: Tool
description: Represents a tool that will be available to workflows.

children.label: schema
description: Tool's input schema, in zod format.

children.label: handler
description:
Handler to call to execute the tool.

Note: if the return type is not a string, it will be stringified when passed down to the LLM

interfaces.label: ToolExecutionNodeConfigType
description: Config for `toolExecution` node type.

interfaces.label: ToolProvider
description:
Represents a tool provider exposed to a workflow to let it call tools.

Tool providers can be either sync or async, to adapt to potential remote implementations.

children.label: has
description: Checks if the registry contains a tool for this ID.

children.label: get
description:
Returns a tool based on its ID

Will throw if no entries are found for the given id.

children.label: getAll
description: Returns all tools that are registered in that registry.

interfaces.label: WorkflowExecutionNodeConfigType
description: Config for `workflowExecution` node type.

interfaces.label: WorkflowExecutionState
description: Meta containing all the info associated with the current execution

children.label: runId
description: The id of this workflow execution run.

children.label: workflowId
description:
ID of the workflow that this error was thrown from.
In case of nested workflows, it will be the ID of the lowest level workflow.

children.label: rootWorkflowId
description: ID of the root workflow, the workflow that was requested to be executed

children.label: stepId
description: If the error occurred during a step execution, this will be the step's ID.

children.label: callChain
description: The whole call chain for this error.

interfaces.label: WorkflowState
description: Represents the workflow state, that gets propagated through nodes during execution.

misc.label: NodeDefinition
description: Describes the configuration structure of a node within a {@link WorkflowDefinition}.

misc.label: NodeFactoryServices
description:
Factory services, composed of the base services and additional services that can be
injected via {@link NodeDefinition.customServicesProvider}

misc.label: NodeProgressionReporterEvent
description:
Subset of the properties of a {@link NodeProgressionEvent} that needs to be specified
by the emitter.
signature: { label: string; data?: Record<string, string> | undefined; }

misc.label: NodeRunnerFactory
description: Represents a factory that can return a runner for a given node type.
